.TH simple_shell 1 "" "Holberton School" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a small shell that reads a line from standard input, parses it into a command and its arguments, and executes it. [web:16]
In interactive mode it displays a prompt and waits for user input; in non\-interactive mode it reads and executes commands until EOF. [web:16][web:21]

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell with an optional status.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment. [web:5]

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the status of the last executed command, or a non\-zero value on error. [web:19]

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1)
